  "prompt": "When will religion cease to exist?",
  "response": "Predicting the future of religion is complex and involves many social, cultural, and personal factors. Religion has been a significant aspect of human civilization for thousands of years, providing community, guidance, moral frameworks, and a sense of purpose for many people.\n\nSome argue that as societies become more secular and scientific understanding advances, traditional religions may decline. Others believe that the need for spirituality and community will ensure that some form of religion continues to exist, even if it evolves or transforms.\n\nUltimately, it is difficult to predict if or when religion might cease to exist, as it is deeply intertwined with human experience and societal structures. Changes in religious belief often occur gradually and are influenced by global events, cultural shifts, and individual experiences.",
